works.description: Brooke Singleton of Dudley Singleton & Daughter hopes to make the most out of the Royal wedding season, as the auctioneer is handling the sale of royal bride-to-be Kate Middleton’s childhood home, where she spent the first 13 years of her life. The four-bedroom Victorian house in the village of Southend Bradfield, 48 miles west of London, will be sold on June 3, about a month after the royal wedding of Prince William and Kate Middleton, which takes place on Friday, April 29 at Westminster Abbey.
